<TITLE> ICC announce World Cup prize-money hike </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Apr 21 (bdnews24.com) -- The winner of the 2011 World Cup will receive more than $4 million in prize-money, after the ICC announced a total pool of $10 million for the competition, double the figure that was in place for the 2007 tournament in the Caribbean, reports Cricinfo. The ICC Board, which met in Dubai on Monday, agreed to the increase "in order to reflect the importance of the ICC's flagship competition." Australia, the winners of the 2007 event, pocketed $2.24 million, with Sri Lanka, the runners-up, taking home $1 million. In 2003, the total prize money was the same, but the percentage handed to the top two teams was less. Australia collected $2 m as champions, while the losing finalists, India, picked up $800
